 _n_ _t_ i from Gautama,  \n35\\. Gautama from Gautama,  \n36\\. Gautama from Vatsya,  \n37\\. Vatsya from Sa _n_ _d_ ilya,  \n38\\. Sa _n_ _d_ ilya from Kai _s_ orya Kapya,  \n39\\. Kai _s_ orya Kapya from Kumaraharita,  \n40\\. Kumaraharita from Galava,  \n41\\. Galava from Vidarbhi-kau _n_ _d_ inya,  \n42\\. Vidarbhi-kau _n_ _d_ inya from Vatsanapat Babhrava,  \n43\\. Vatsanapat Babhrava from Pathi Saubhara,  \n44\\. Pathi Saubhara from Ayasya \xc3\x82\xe1\xb9\x85girasa,  \n45\\. Ayasya \xc3\x82\xe1\xb9\x85girasa from \xc3\x82bhuti Tvash _t_ ra,  \n46\\. \xc3\x82bhuti Tvash _t_ ra from Vi _s_ varupa Tvash _t_ ra,  \n47\\. Vi _s_ varupa Tvash _t_ ra from A _s_ vinau,  \n48\\. A _s_ vinau from Dadhya _k_ \xc3\x82tharva _n_ a,  \n49\\. Dadhya _k_ \xc3\x82tharva _n_ a from Atharvan Daiva,  \n50\\. Atharvan Daiva from M _ri_ tyu Pradhva _m_ sana,  \n51\\. M _ri_ tyu Pradhva _m_ sana from Pradhva _m_ sana,  \n52\\. Pradhva _m_ sana from Ekarshi,  \n53\\. Ekarshi from Vipra _k_ itti 2,  \n54\\. Vipra _k_ itti from Vyash _t_ i,\n\n\n\np. 188\n\n55\\. Vyash _t_ i from Sanaru,  \n56\\. Sanaru from Sanatana,  \n57\\. Sanatana from Sanaga,  \n58\\. Sanaga from Paramesh _th_ in,  \n59\\. Paramesh _th_ in from Brahman,  \n60\\. Brahman is Svayambhu, self-existent.  \nAdoration to Brahman.\n\n\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[185:1](sbe15077.htm#fr_544) See B _ri_ h. Up. III, 9, 26; IV, 2, 4; IV, 4,\n22.\n\n[185:2](sbe15078.htm#fr_545) The line of teachers and pupils by whom the Ya\n_g_ _\xc3\xb1_ avalkya-ka _n_ _d_ a p. 186 was handed down. From 1-10 the Va _m_ _s_\na agrees with the Va _m_ _s_ a at the end of II, 6.\n\nThe Madhyandina text begins with vayam, we, and proceeds to 1. Saurpa _n_\nayya, 2. Gautama, 3. Vatsya, 4. Para _s_ arya, &c., as in the Madhuka _n_ _d_\na, p. 118, except in 10, where it gives _G_ aivantayana for \xc3\x82treya. Then after\n12. Kau _n_ _d_ inyayana, it gives 13. 14. the two Kau _n_ _d_ inyas, 15. the\nAur _n_ avabhas, 16. Kau _n_ _d_ inya, 17. Kau _n_ _d_ inya, 18. Kau _n_ _d_\ninya and \xc3\x82gnivesya, 19. Saitava, 20. Para _s_ arya, 2 1. _G_ atukar _n_ ya,\n22. Bharadva _g_ a, 2 3. Bharadva _g_ a, \xc3\x82suraya _n_ a, and Gautama, 24.\nBharadva _g_ a, 25. Valakakau _s_ ika, 26. Kashaya _n_ a, 27. Saukaraya _n_ a,\n28. Traiva _n_ i, 29. Aupa _g_ andhani, 30. Sayakayana, p. Kau _s_ ikayani,\n&c., as in the Ka _n_ va text, from No. 22 to Brahman.\n\n[186:1](sbe15078.htm#fr_546) From here the Va _m_ _s_ a agrees again with that\ngiven at the end of II, 6.\n\n[187:1](sbe15078.htm#fr_547) The Madhyandina text has, 1. Bharadva _g_ a, 2.\nBharadva _g_ a, \xc3\x82suraya _n_ a, and Yaska.\n\n[187:2](sbe15078.htm#fr_548) Vipra _g_ itti, Madhyandina text.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: V, 1](sbe15079.htm)\n\n'